headline.main: ITALIAN MORALE IS HELD CRACKING; Turks Hear Military Courts Are Trying 'Defeatists' -- 3 Guillotined in France

lead_paragraph: ANKARA, Turkey, Sept. 26 -- Reports received in foreign diplomatic and military circles here and in Istanbul indicate there has been a new outbreak of demonstrations and a sharp decline in morale in Italy.
abstract: Rising unrest and decline in morale reptd in Italy; disorders in Croatia assume civil war proportions; rept of Ital plan to place Dr V Matchek, former Peasant Party Premier, at head of puppet Croat Govt denied by Ankara Croatian circles
